# Use lenient peer-dependency resolution for every install (local + CI).
#
# Some transitive packages declare overlapping peer ranges that newer npm
# versions (npm 7+) treat as a hard ERESOLVE error, which aborts a clean
# `npm install` — e.g. the GitHub Actions APK build and the in-app "update",
# both of which install against a fresh tree with no relaxation. Locally the
# resolution happens to succeed, so this only bites on clean/CI installs.
#
# `legacy-peer-deps=true` restores the npm 6 behaviour (peer deps are not
# auto-installed and conflicts don't fail the install), giving a durable,
# npm-version-proof safety net so updates and CI builds stay green.
legacy-peer-deps=true
